user_question: If two galaxies were to collide, what would happen to their stars and planets?
final_answer: When two galaxies collide, their stars and planets generally do not collide directly due to the vast distances between them. Instead, gravitational interactions can lead to new star formation and changes in the orbits of stars and planets.
